# Q: Find the command that kills the background commandâ€™s process
sudo kill -KILL $(jobs -p)
# 0: send a signal to a process 
# 1: -KILL cannot be blocked
# 2: of jobs: displaying status of jobs in teh current session
# 3: -p dispalys only the process ID of the process group leader of the jobs. 
